                    <div>
                        <article>
<div>
<div align="left"><span style="font-size: medium;">Hello fellow ench. Enchanter is Job in Iruna that utilize gear to dealt damage also for their defense. I believe you know that <a href="http://www.iruna-online.info/&nbsp;" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener">www.iruna-online.info/&nbsp;</a> provide many information about weapon, armor, etc stats also its hidden, but there are no enchanter gear review ( autoskill damage, proc rate, etc). In this thread, I will review some enchanter gear. Remember, I only give stats to some gear that try before.<br /></span></div>
<div align="left"><span style="font-size: medium;">Here explanation for stats grade classification:</span></div>
<br />
<div><a style="display: none;">SPOILER: Click to show</a><span style="cursor: pointer;"><span style="font-size: large;"><strong>Damage:</strong></span></span></div>
<div data-tag="spoiler">A = &gt;100k<br />B = 70k-100k<br />C = 50k-70k<br />D = 30k-50k<br />E = &lt;30k</div>
<div><a style="display: none;">SPOILER: Click to show</a><span style="cursor: pointer;"><strong><span style="font-size: large;">Proc Rate (Base):</span></strong></span></div>
<div data-tag="spoiler">A = &gt;50%<br />B = 30%-50%<br />C = 15%-30%<br />D = 5%-15%<br />E = &lt;5%</div>
<div><a style="display: none;">SPOILER: Click to show</a><span style="cursor: pointer;"><span style="font-size: large;"><strong>Survival:</strong></span></span></div>
<div data-tag="spoiler">A = &gt; 1 either Magic R+, Melee R+, Absolute Eva+, Magic Eva+, or defensive autoskill<br />B = Has 1 either Magic R+, Melee R+, Absolute Eva+, Magic Eva+, or defensive autoskill<br />C = No Survival Function<br />D = Has 1 either Magic R-, Melee R+, Absolute Eva-, Magic Eva-<br />E = &gt; 1 either Magic R-, Melee R-, Absolute Eva-, Magic Eva-</div>
<div><a style="display: none;">SPOILER: Click to show</a><span style="cursor: pointer;"><span style="font-size: large;"><strong>Stats:</strong></span></span></div>
<div data-tag="spoiler">A = Impressive for DPS/Survival<br />B = Good for DPS/Survival<br />C = Just Okay<br />D = Not Really Good<br />E = Meh</div>
<div align="left"><strong><span style="font-size: medium;">Overall Grade:</span></strong></div>
<div align="left"><span style="font-size: medium;">&gt;8.0 = Must Have xD<br /></span></div>
<div align="left"><span style="font-size: medium;">7.0 - 8.0 = Recommended</span></div>
<div align="left"><span style="font-size: medium;">4.0 - 7.0 = Worth to Buy</span></div>
<div align="left"><span style="font-size: medium;">&lt;4.0 = Not worth<br /></span></div>
<div align="left"><span style="font-size: medium;"><span style="font-size: medium;">So lets start the review<span style="font-size: small;"><br /></span></span></span>
<div><a style="display: none;">SPOILER: Click to show</a><span style="cursor: pointer;"><span style="font-size: x-large;"><strong><span style="font-size: xx-large;">Magic Attack Gears</span></strong><span style="font-size: xx-small;">click here for spoiler</span></span></span></div>
<div data-tag="spoiler"><span style="font-size: small;">Gear with Magic attack chance stats. These gear autoskill will activated when you do normal attack. Dual Blow will be counted as two normal attack, so dual blow will increase number autoskill that proc at that time. Each gear has its own autoskill damage, proc rate, and even hidden stats.</span></div>
</div>
<div>
<div><a style="display: none;">SPOILER: Click to show</a><span style="cursor: pointer;"><span style="font-size: large;"><strong>Weapon</strong></span></span></div>
<div data-tag="spoiler"><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-size: small;"><strong>Lists:</strong><br /></span></span>
<div><a style="display: none;">SPOILER: Click to show</a><span style="cursor: pointer;"><strong>Dim Sword IV (Swords)</strong></span></div>
<div data-tag="spoiler"><strong>Autoskill:</strong> Dark Javelin [Dark Element Magic]<br /><strong>Damage :</strong> A+<br /><strong>Proc Rate :</strong> D<br /><strong>Survival :</strong> C<br /><strong>Stats :</strong> C<br /><strong>Overall:</strong> 8.0<br /><strong>Description:</strong> ATK: 235 Magic Sword, All stats +5 Hidden: When attacking, chance of magic attack<br /><strong>Complete:</strong> STR +5 AGI +5 VIT +5 INT +5 DEX +5 CRT +5 Autoskill<br /><strong>Review:</strong> Dark element magic autoskill sword. For now, this weapon deal highest raw autoskill damage, as high as Dajarte but without negatives. However this sword has mediocre stats and low autoskill proc rate. This sword will be shine in Special Status condition.<br /><br /></div>
<div><a style="display: none;">SPOILER: Click to show</a><span style="cursor: pointer;"><strong>Gram (Swords)</strong></span></div>
<div data-tag="spoiler"><strong>Autoskill:</strong> Dark Blast [Dark Element Magic ; +50% own Autoskill Damage vs Melee Barrier]<br /><strong>Damage :</strong> B<br /><strong>Proc Rate :</strong> B<br /><strong>Survival : </strong>C<br /><strong>Stats : </strong>A<br /><strong>Overall :</strong> 9.0<br /><strong>Description:</strong> ATK: 300 Magic Sword, Dark Element, Spell Burst +10%, ATK +16%, MATK +16%, Autoskill +3%, Magic attack chance.<br /><strong>Complete:</strong> Melee to Light +20% ATK +16% MATK +16% Autoskill +3% Spellburst +10% Autoskill<br /><strong>Review:</strong> Dark element magic autoskill sword. This sword stats is perfect for enchanter. ATK &amp; MATK +16% with +10% Spell Burst will make you dealt high damage on boss. But its autoskill damage just rank B which quite average for Magic autoskill damage, even tough Gram autoskill damage can be reach rank A if you against melee barrier boss/mob.<br /><br /></div>
<div><a style="display: none;">SPOILER: Click to show</a><span style="cursor: pointer;"><strong>Eraser (Sword)</strong></span></div>
<div data-tag="spoiler"><strong>Autoskill :</strong> Dark Blast [Dark Element Magic]; Dark R&gt;25%, then Heal HP by Attack<br /><strong>Damage :</strong> E<br /><strong>Proc Rate :</strong> A<br /><strong>Survival : </strong>B+<br /><strong>Stats :</strong> B<br /><strong>Overall :</strong> 7.0<br /><strong>Description:</strong> ATK: 301 Magic sword, Dark element, MATK +15%, Chance to activate Darkness lv1. The effect depends on Dark R..<br /><strong>Complete:</strong> Melee to Light +20% MATK +15% Autoskill <br /><strong>Review:</strong> This weapon autoskill damage is terrible (equal with Enfar and Avazel lol). But dont get fooled with that low autoskill damage. This sword has hidden &ldquo;Heal HP by attack with 100% proc rate if you had minimum 20%-25% Dark Resistance&rdquo;. This sword heal based your 10% your normal attack damage. Looks useless since Enchanter Normal attack damage is terrible, but still helpful if you against boss that can frequently do Special attack directly on HP ignoring any defensive mechanics. Maybe this Magic Sword DPS will be better for INT Samurai or CRT Ench :v. .<br /><br /></div>
<div><a style="display: none;">SPOILER: Click to show</a><span style="cursor: pointer;"><strong>Earthquake Bell (Canes)</strong></span></div>
<div data-tag="spoiler"><strong>Autoskill :</strong> Earthquake [Earth Element Magic]<br /><strong>Damage :</strong> A<br /><strong>Proc Rate :</strong> B<br /><strong>Survival : </strong>C<br /><strong>Stats :</strong> B+<br /><strong>Overall :</strong> 9.0<br /><strong>Description:</strong> ATK: 277-283 DEF: 15 Earth magic +20% MATK +8% Autoskills +5%, Magic attack chance by attack<br /><strong>Complete:</strong> Earth Magic +20% MATK +8% Autoskill +5% Autoskill<br /><strong>Review:</strong> Earth magic autoskill rod. One of most balanced enchanter weapon with high autoskill damage. EQ autoskill damage almost as high as dajarte, but no negatives. This rod will be shine at Earth autoskill magic set (which means you need cherose). This rod almost had no negatives.<br /><br /></div>
<div><a style="display: none;">SPOILER: Click to show</a><span style="cursor: pointer;"><strong>Caliburn (Swords)</strong></span></div>
<div data-tag="spoiler"><strong>Autoskill :</strong> Nemesis ; Cross Counter [Light Element Magic ; Cross Counter by defense]<br /><strong>Damage :</strong> B-<br /><strong>Proc Rate :</strong> C<br /><strong>Survival : </strong>A<br /><strong>Stats : </strong>A<br /><strong>Overall :</strong> 8.0<br /><strong>Description: </strong>ATK: 275-290-305 Magic Sword, Light Element, MATK +15%, Melee R +10%, Magic R +10%, Magic Attack Chance by Attack<br /><strong>Complete:</strong> Melee to Dark +20% MATK +15% Melee R +10% Magic R +10% Autoskill MaxHP +30%<br /><strong>Review:</strong> This sword function is for defensive purpose, however this sword can become Light element autoskill damage set for enchanter. In my opinion, this sword is great for semi-defensive set since you can use this sword with Wizard Crysta for more magic resistance and Light magic boost purpose.<br /><br /></div>
<div><a style="display: none;">SPOILER: Click to show</a><span style="cursor: pointer;"><strong>Giblekening (Swords)</strong></span></div>
<div data-tag="spoiler"><strong>Autoskill :</strong> Blizzard [Water Element Magic]<br /><strong>Damage :</strong> B<br /><strong>Proc Rate :</strong> C<br /><strong>Survival : </strong>C<br /><strong>Stats : </strong>B<strong><br />Overall : </strong>7.5<br /><strong>Description:</strong> ATK: 250 Magic Sword, ASPD +20%, MATK +6%, Magic attack chance by attack, Small ATK up by Lv, Small MATK up by Lv<br /><strong>Complete:</strong> ASPD +20% MATK +6% Autoskill [X = 0.40 * Lv] [ATK up by X] [X = 0.50 * Lv] [MATK up by X]<br /><strong>Review:</strong> Magic sword with Water element magic autoskill. Nothing special with this weapon unless you pair this sword with Cataract Helm. This sword autoskill damage is lower than Cherose but higher than Leviathan.<br /><br /></div>
<div><a style="display: none;">SPOILER: Click to show</a><span style="cursor: pointer;"><strong>Etincelle (Swords)</strong></span></div>
<div data-tag="spoiler"><strong>Autoskill :</strong> Meteor [Fire Element Magic]<br /><strong>Damage :</strong> B+<br /><strong>Proc Rate : </strong>B<br /><strong>Survival :</strong> D+<br /><strong>Stats :</strong> B<br /><strong>Overall :</strong> 8.0<br /><strong>Description: </strong>ATK: 240 Flame element, fire magic up by STR, Burn rate +5%, Magic pierce +16%, MATK +7%, Magic Sword<br /><strong>Complete:</strong> Melee to Earth +20% Melee to Fire +10% MATK +7% Burn +5% Magic Pierce +16% [X = 0.02 * STR] [X + 5] [Fire Magic up by X] Autoskill Melee R -15% If [Mage] then Autoskill +5%<strong><br />Review: </strong>Magic sword with Fire element magic autoskill. This sword actually is good especially for beginner since this sword is cheap. Has good autoskill damage and proc rate due to its hidden Autoskill +5%. However, its Melee R -15% makes this sword sometimes risky to use against physical based boss.<br /><br /></div>
<div><a style="display: none;">SPOILER: Click to show</a><span style="cursor: pointer;"><strong>Eve Pramia (Claws)</strong></span></div>
<div data-tag="spoiler"><strong>Autoskill :</strong> Meteor [Fire Element Magic]<br /><strong>Damage :</strong> B+<br /><strong>Proc Rate : </strong>B<br /><strong>Survival :</strong> D+<br /><strong>Stats :</strong> C<br /><strong>Overall :</strong> 8.0<br /><strong>Description: </strong>ATK: 268 DEF: 3 MATK +10%, Critical damage -5%, magic through +10%, Critical rate +30, Magic R -10%, Magic attack chance by attack<br /><strong>Complete:</strong> MATK +10% Magic Pierce +10% Critical rate +30 Critical damage -5% Magic R -10% Autoskill +5% Autoskill <strong><br />Review: </strong>Fire magic autoskill claws. This is one of infamous old day enchanter weapons. Its stats is inferior compared to other nowday famous ench weapon. But with correct gear setup, its damage can be equal with Dajarte that fully buffed with Ghost Ring up autoskill + Pauk al (but no struggler MATK steroid). Sadly, you will not have high MATK if use this weapon because this is claw weapon (which means no struggler) and no magic weapon attribute (which means you will not get extra ATK &amp; MATK from enchant skill). However, maybe this weapon will get huge benefit when new add gear from lv400 Flammel released.<br /><br /></div>
<div><a style="display: none;">SPOILER: Click to show</a><span style="cursor: pointer;"><strong>Dia Espada (Strengthened 1) (Swords)</strong></span></div>
<div data-tag="spoiler"><strong>Autoskill : </strong>Mana Wave [Non-Element Magic]<br /><strong>Damage : </strong>E<br /><strong>Proc Rate :</strong> A<br /><strong>Survival : </strong>C<br /><strong>Stats :</strong> C<br /><strong>Overall : </strong>4.0<strong><br />Description: </strong>ATK: 195 magic sword MATK +5% probability magic attack no magic +20%<br /><strong>Complete: </strong>MATK +5% Neutral Magic +20% Autoskill<br /><strong>Notes:</strong> Trade &times;<strong><br />Review: </strong>An infamous old day enchanter weapon. Magic sword with neutral type magic autoskill. This weapon proc rate is very high, however its damage is very low. After enchanter Origin skill update which increase elemental magic damage from autoskill and change magic blade element type, this weapon isnt relevant again either for Auto Attack or Magic Blade enchanter.<br /><br /></div>
<span style="font-size: small;">.<br /></span></div>
<div><a style="display: none;">SPOILER: Click to show</a><span style="cursor: pointer;"><span style="font-size: large;"><strong>Additional Gear</strong></span></span></div>
<div data-tag="spoiler"><span style="font-size: small;"><strong>Lists:</strong></span><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="font-size: small;"><br /></span></span>
<div><a style="display: none;">SPOILER: Click to show</a><span style="cursor: pointer;"><strong>Fallen Angel Wing (Additional)</strong></span></div>
<div data-tag="spoiler"><strong>Autoskill :</strong> Dark Javelin [Dark Element Magic ; +50% own Autoskill damage vs Melee Barrier]<br /><strong>Damage :</strong> B<br /><strong>Proc Rate :</strong> B<br /><strong>Survival :</strong> C<br /><strong>Stats :</strong> A<br /><strong>Overall :</strong> 8.0<br /><strong>Description:</strong> DEF: 5-11-25 MATK +20%, MaxMP +20%, Melee to Light +10%, Magic Attack Chance by Attack.<br /><strong>Complete:</strong> MATK +20% MaxMP +20% Melee to Light +10% Autoskill<br /><strong>Review:</strong> Dark magic autoskill gear. This add has highest MATK boost compared to other additional gear, also give autoskill chance by attack. However, its autoskill damage is similar with Gram (rank B against non-melee barrier but rank A against melee barrier). This gear price is ridiculous for beginner (1b+), so dont recommended for beginner until you had complete Dark set.<br /><br /></div>
<div><a style="display: none;">SPOILER: Click to show</a><span style="cursor: pointer;"><strong>Angel Ring (Additional)</strong></span></div>
<div data-tag="spoiler"><strong>Autoskill :</strong> Nemesis [Light Element Magic]<strong><br />Damage :</strong> B<br /><strong>Proc Rate :</strong> C<br /><strong>Survival :</strong> C<br /><strong>Stats :</strong> A<br /><strong>Overall :</strong> 7.5<br /><strong>Description:</strong> DEF: 18 Light magic +3% MATK +15% Heal recovery +10% Magic attack chance by attack<br /><strong>Complete:</strong> Light Magic +3% MATK +15% Heal Recovery +10% Autoskill<br /><strong>Review:</strong> Light magic autoskill additional gear. Normally, Light autoskill damage is weak compared to another element (only Neutral magic autoskill that has lower damage than Light). However Angel Ring autoskill is exception. Its auto can be compared with another element magic without its origin level(except dark and earth autoskill). Also this gear is Important piece to make semi-defensive set that I mention in Caliburn. Put Wizard to this add for more magic resistance and Light magic boost.<br /><br /></div>
<div><a style="display: none;">SPOILER: Click to show</a><span style="cursor: pointer;"><strong>Cataract Helm (Additional)</strong></span></div>
<div data-tag="spoiler"><strong>Autoskill :</strong> Blizzard [Water Element Magic]<br /><strong>Damage : </strong>B+<br /><strong>Proc Rate :</strong> C<br /><strong>Survival :</strong> C<br /><strong>Stats :</strong> B<br /><strong>Overall :</strong> 7.5<br /><strong>Description:</strong> DEF: 16-22 when ATK &bull; MATK +5% Heal reward +10% attack, magic attack with probability (hidden correction: water magic +10%?)<br /><strong>Complete:</strong> ATK +5% MATK +5% Heal Reward +10% Autoskill If [Lv &gt; 250] then Water Magic +10%<br /><strong>Review:</strong> Water autoskill magic additional gear. Personally I never try this gear, but since I heard this add auto damage is higher than Giblekening, I decided to put this gear to list. This gear stats is inferior compared to Sage Hat reup. But since its has autoskill that beat gible, I think this gear will increase DPS from Water set.<br /><br /></div>
<div><a style="display: none;">SPOILER: Click to show</a><span style="cursor: pointer;"><strong>Magia Hood (Strengthened 1) (Additional)</strong></span></div>
<div data-tag="spoiler"><strong>Autoskill :</strong> Meteor; Blizzard; Thor Hammer; Earthquake; Nemesis; Dark Javelin [Random elemental magic]<br /><strong>Damage :</strong> B-<br /><strong>Proc Rate :</strong> C<br /><strong>Survival :</strong> C<br /><strong>Stats :</strong> C<br /><strong>Overall :</strong> 7.0<br /><strong>Description:</strong> DEF: 13-15 when MaxHP &bull; MP increases MP cost -15% attack as Lv, magic attack with probability<br /><strong>Complete: </strong>[MaxHP up by Lv] [MaxMP up by Lv] MP Cost -15% Critical rate -15% [Adventurer] Autoskill Autoskill Autoskill Autoskill Autoskill Autoskill<br /><strong>Review:</strong> Random magic autoskill additional gear. This gear is good for beginner since you don't need buy magic autoskill crysta to your additional gear slot. However, this gear autoskill is unstable. Also, because ench has Origin skill, this gear will be outperformed by specific element additional gear &amp; crysta.</div>
</div>
<div><a style="display: none;">SPOILER: Click to show</a><span style="cursor: pointer;"><span style="font-size: large;"><strong>Special Equipment</strong></span></span></div>
