<div><a style="display: none;">SPOILER: Click to show</a><span style="cursor: pointer;"><strong>◇ Ifrit (Crystas)</strong></span></div>
<div data-tag="spoiler"><strong>Autoskill :</strong> Fire Lance [Fire Element Magic]<br /><strong>Damage :</strong> C<br /><strong>Proc Rate :</strong> C<br /><strong>Survival :</strong> C<br /><strong>Stats :</strong> C<br /><strong>Overall : </strong>7.0<strong><br />Description: </strong>Adds Fire element magic attack on equipment. (Consumes autoskill)<br /><br /></div>
<div><a style="display: none;">SPOILER: Click to show</a><span style="cursor: pointer;"><strong>◇ Leviathan (Crystas)</strong></span></div>
<div data-tag="spoiler"><strong>Autoskill :</strong> Ice Spear [Water Element Magic]<br /><strong>Damage :</strong> C<br /><strong>Proc Rate :</strong> C<br /><strong>Survival :</strong> C<br /><strong>Stats :</strong> C<br /><strong>Overall :</strong> 7.0<br /><strong>Description:</strong> Adds Water magic attack on equipment. (Consumes autoskill)<br /><br /></div>
<div><a style="display: none;">SPOILER: Click to show</a><span style="cursor: pointer;"><strong>◇ Pretortoise (Crystas)</strong></span></div>
<div data-tag="spoiler"><strong>Autoskill :</strong> Thunderbolt [Wind Element Magic]<strong><br />Damage :</strong> C<br /><strong>Proc Rate :</strong> C<br /><strong>Survival :</strong> B (thanks to origin lv.3 :v)<br /><strong>Stats :</strong> C<br /><strong>Overall :</strong> 7.5<br /><strong>Description:</strong> It adds a magic attack of Wind element to Equipment ※ Autoskills of equipment point will disappear.</div>
<div><a style="display: none;">SPOILER: Click to show</a><span style="cursor: pointer;"><strong>Review</strong> (for 3 Crysta above): </span></div>
<div data-tag="spoiler">These crystal has same aspect, so I compile these three xtall. Both Ifrit, Leviathan, and Pretortoise has same stats, damage output, and autoskill proc rate. The only aspect that make each xtall different is their element, Ifrit is Fire element, Leviathan is Water element, and Pretortoise is Wind element. However, Pretortoise has more advantage for some enchanter because you can use Origin lv 3 to increase its damage, which means more Thunderbolt autoskill will be proc. Please note that Pretortoise cant paralyze enemy, paralyze status comes from Thunderbolt autoskill.<br /><br /></div>
<div><a style="display: none;">SPOILER: Click to show</a><span style="cursor: pointer;"><strong>◇ Cherose (Crystas)</strong></span></div>
<div data-tag="spoiler"><strong>Autoskill :</strong> Earthquake [Earth Element Magic]<strong><br />Damage :</strong> B+<br /><strong>Proc Rate :</strong> C<br /><strong>Survival :</strong> C<br /><strong>Stats :</strong> C<br /><strong>Overall :</strong> 8.0<br /><strong>Description:</strong> Earth magic attack chance by attack (Consumes autoskill).<br /><strong>Review: </strong>Earth element magic autoskill xtall. Different from default Magic elemental xtall, Cherose damage is surpisingly high. Cherose damage only lose to Dajarte in term of higest autoskill damage from xtall. After Earthquake Bell released, Cherose damage become more powerful. Moreover, you can use Origin lv 4 to increase Cherose damage which means more chance to stun enemies via Earth Pike autoskill. Cherose is one reason why Earth magic autoskill become as powerful as Dark magic autoskill.<br /><br /></div>
<div><a style="display: none;">SPOILER: Click to show</a><span style="cursor: pointer;"><strong>◇ Gewalt (Crystas)</strong></span></div>
<div data-tag="spoiler"><strong>Autoskill :</strong> Nemesis [Light Element Magic]<strong><br />Damage :</strong> C<br /><strong>Proc Rate :</strong> C<br /><strong>Survival :</strong> C<br /><strong>Stats :</strong> C<br /><strong>Overall :</strong> 7.0<br /><strong>Description:</strong> Adds Light element magic on equipment. (Consumes autoskill).<br /><strong>Review: </strong>Light element magic autoskill xtall. I believe that someone in this forum has test Gewalt. Gewalt damage is inferior compared to other magic autoskill xtall, it because ench has no skill to increase Light elemental magic damage. Fortunately, with right equipment, Light magic set can dealt 60k-80k damage/auto (no spellburst). But, you need some expensive stuff to make Gewalt become effective (see my Angel ring and Caliburn review).<br /><br /></div>
<div><a style="display: none;">SPOILER: Click to show</a><span style="cursor: pointer;"><strong>◇ Dajarte (Crystas)</strong></span></div>
<div data-tag="spoiler"><strong>Autoskill :</strong> Dark Javelin [Dark Element Magic]<strong><br />Damage :</strong> A+<br /><strong>Proc Rate :</strong> D<br /><strong>Survival :</strong> E<br /><strong>Stats :</strong> B<br /><strong>Overall :</strong> 9.0<br /><strong>Description:</strong> Magic R -11%, Magic evasion -11%, Attack +11%, Put dark magic attack on the equipment. (Consumes autoskill)<br /><strong>Review: </strong>Dark element magic autoskill xtall. Highest autoskill damage so far with poor autoskill proc rate. Dajarte damage is based on ATK &amp; MATK which suitable with ench stats. But please remember that Dajarte has -11% Magic Evasion &amp; Magic Resistance which will hurt your survivalbiliy.<br /><br /></div>
<div><a style="display: none;">SPOILER: Click to show</a><span style="cursor: pointer;"><strong>◇ Enfar (Crystas)</strong></span></div>
<div data-tag="spoiler"><strong>Autoskill :</strong> Dark Blast [Dark Element Magic]<strong><br />Damage :</strong> E<br /><strong>Proc Rate :</strong> A<br /><strong>Survival :</strong> C<br /><strong>Stats :</strong> D<br /><strong>Overall :</strong> 4.0<br /><strong>Description:</strong> Dark magic attack chance by attack (Temporarily consumes autoskill).<br /><strong>Review: </strong>Dark element magic autoskill xtall. Contrast with Dajarte, Enfar autoskill damage is lowest among all Magic Attack crysta with amazing proc rate. Eventhough it says temporarily consumes autoskill, in fact, this crysta consume autoskill since I never saw my auto from gear where I placed this crysta with proc. Not worth for Enchanter.<br /><br /></div>
<div><a style="display: none;">SPOILER: Click to show</a><span style="cursor: pointer;"><strong>◇ Avazel (Crystas)</strong></span></div>
<div data-tag="spoiler"><strong>Autoskill :</strong> Dark Blast [Dark Element Magic]<strong><br />Damage :</strong> E<br /><strong>Proc Rate :</strong> A<br /><strong>Survival :</strong> C<br /><strong>Stats :</strong> D<br /><strong>Overall :</strong> 4.0<br /><strong>Description:</strong> Dark magic +6%, Melee +6 to Light, Magic attack chance by attack (Consumes autoskill).<br /><strong>Review: </strong>Another crysta with lowish autoskill damage. Nothing to says but meh ._____________________________.</div>
</div>
